   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1813-08-25_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="Id_where"/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth Town</placeName>
                  <date when="1813-08-25">Aug<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.. 1813
               </date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>Dear Madam</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am not sure whether your present <choice>
                  <orig>resi<lb/>
               dence</orig>
                  <reg>residence</reg>
               </choice> at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Hampstead_ENK">Hampstead</placeName> will make it <choice>
                  <orig>incon<lb/>
               venient</orig>
                  <reg>inconvenient</reg>
               </choice> to you to execute some <choice>
                  <orig>commiss<lb/>
               ions</orig>
                  <reg>commissions</reg>
               </choice> for us in Town; but if it should be<lb/>
               so I hope you will have no scruple in<lb/>
               telling <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Edgeworth</persName> and I so and we<lb/>
               will apply to some other friend<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               But if it should be perfectly <choice>
                  <orig>con<lb/>
               venient</orig>
                  <reg>convenient</reg>
               </choice> to you to go to Town we should<lb/>
               be much obliged to you if you could get<lb/>
               us some things in the choice of which we<lb/>
               wish to depend on your taste. They can<lb/>
               be sent well packed in a parcel directed<lb/>
               to me to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StrutW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W. Strutt's</persName> correspondent in<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> - I left the direction to his house<lb/>
               with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> and he can give it to you<lb/>
               They send a parcel to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StrutW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W. Strutt</persName> - <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Helens-House_ENK">S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. <choice>
                     <orig>Hel=<lb/>
                  lens</orig>
                     <reg>Helen's</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName> near <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Derby_ENK">Derby</placeName> every week and if you<lb/>
               send the parcel <add>as <hi rend="underline">soon</hi> as you can</add> directed for me<lb/>
               <del>at</del> to be <choice>
                  <orig>for=<lb/>
                  warded</orig>
                  <reg>forwarded</reg>
               </choice> to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StrutW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W. Strutts</persName>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Helens-House_ENK">St. <choice>
                     <orig>Hellens</orig>
                     <reg>Helen's</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Derby_ENK">Derby</placeName> I<lb/>           
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1813-08-25_page02.jpg"/>
               I will write to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StrutW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Strutt</persName> to have it sent over<lb/>
               from thence to me by my brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> who<lb/>
               <del>will</del> is now at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Derby_ENK">Derby</placeName> and will soon <choice>
                  <orig>re=<lb/>
               turn</orig>
                  <reg>return</reg>
               </choice> to us - If you will be so good to let<lb/>
               me know by post the amount of the money<lb/>
               you lay out for us or the amount of the<lb/>
               bills I will take care to send you a draft<lb/>
               on <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HoarC1">Hoare</persName> for the money by return of the<lb/>
               post -
            </p>
            <p>
               We have never yet heard more of our<lb/>
               trunks than that they were shipped at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Liverpool_ENK">Liverpool</placeName> by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GreaJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. J. Greaves</persName> - even in what<lb/>
               vessel we are ignorant, and we have been<lb/>
               at considerable inconvenience for want<lb/>
               of our clothes -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               As I have not had the M<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Patro1">
                  <hi rend="underline">Patronage</hi>
               </title> to<lb/>
               correct I fear it will be impossible for me<lb/>
               even if I should at last receive it safely to<lb/>
               return it corrected in time for Xmas<lb/>
               publication -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I am sure that you and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<lb/>
               Hunter</persName> will hear with pleasure that my<lb/>
               brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> is just going to be married<lb/>
               to the satisfaction of all his family to <del>
                  <unclear/>
               </del>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH3">Miss <choice>
                     <orig>Broadhearst</orig>
                     <reg>Broadhurst</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Derbyshire_ENK">Derbyshire</placeName> (sister of the member for<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Weymouth_ENK">Weymouth</placeName>
               <lb/>           
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1813-08-25_page03.jpg"/>
               lady of very amiable character, to whom he <del>has</del>
               <lb/>
               is much attached and who has besides other<lb/>
               good things a <hi rend="underline">reasonably</hi> good fortune of<lb/>
               I believe about a thousand a year - not enough<lb/>
               to make him <damage><unclear><gap></gap> profession</unclear></damage> - but<lb/>
               sufficient to enable him to marry without<lb/>
               imprudence<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               With best wishes for your health &amp; hap-<lb/>
               piness &amp; that of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> &amp; your children<lb/>
               I am Dear Madam<lb/>
               Your <choice>
                  <orig>Obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>obedient</reg>
               </choice>
               <choice>
                  <orig>Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>servant</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Miles</persName>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Pauls-Churchyard_ENK">S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. <unclear>Paul</unclear>'s Church Yard</placeName>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
               </address>
            </closer>
         </div>
